content.description: Sit Start on a nice low ledge, avoid the ledge holds out left and work your way straight up right and to the arete. Crux is getting to a nice sloper pocket for your right hand mid way up the corner. Easy climbing to the top from there.
content.location: Walking along the main trail, you'll see a hallway in the middle of the warm up boulder. Keep walking down the halway until it ends. Panic room is on the arete at the end of the halway.

content.description: Sit start on two very chalked holds and bad feet under the roof, traverse to the right then left out the lip of the roof. Start the top-out once you reach a good nob hold. Hard mantle move to the ledge.
content.protection: Couple of pads. It's a flat landing.
content.location: On the lower side of the Warmup Boulders, across the creek from Riverside and next to a fire pit. Look for the graffiti Eye of Providence above the problem.

content.description: Sit start on crimps about a foot below the starting holds of the normal Doppelgänger start. Make a few moves up the face.
content.location: On the back side of the warmup cluster of boulders. It will be just to your right along the main trail after you pass the warmup cluster.

content.description: Tightly packed cluster of boulders offering a ton of great warm ups.
